<docs>
	<doc for="ColumnHeader.ToString"><nodoc/>
		<summary>
   Returns a string representation of this column header
   </summary>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader.ColumnHeader">
		<summary>
			<para>Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> class.</para>
		</summary>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader.Text">
		<summary>
			<para>Gets or sets the text displayed in the column header.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>The text displayed in the column header.</para>
		</value>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader.Clone">
		<summary>
			<para>Creates an identical copy of the current <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> that is not attached to any list view 
   control.</para>
		</summary>
		<returns>
			<para>An object representing a copy of this <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> object.</para>
		</returns>
		<remarks>
			<para>You can use this method to copy existing <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> objects from an existing <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> 
control for use in other <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> controls.</para>
		</remarks>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader.ShouldPersistText">
		<summary>
			<para>Indicates whether the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Text"/> property should be
   persisted.</para>
		</summary>
		<returns>
			<para><see langword="true"/> if the property value has changed
   from its default; otherwise, <see langword="false"/> .</para>
		</returns>
		<remarks>
			<para>You typically use this method if you are either creating
      a designer for the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> or creating your own control incorporating
      the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/>.</para>
		</remarks>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Text"/>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader.TextAlign">
		<summary>
			<para>Gets or sets the horizontal alignment of the text 
      displayed in the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> .</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>One of the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.HorizontalAlignment"/> values. The default is
<see langword="HorizontalAlignment.Left"/>.</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>You can use this property to provide different text alignment settings for 
      the text displayed in each <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/>. For example, you might
      want to align the first <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> in a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> control to the left while
      keeping the rest of the fields center or right aligned.</para>
		</remarks>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.HorizontalAlignment"/>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader.ListView">
		<summary>
			<para>Gets the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> control the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> is located in.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>A <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> control that represents the control that
   contains the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> .</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>You can use this property to determine which <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> control a specific 
<see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> object is associated with.</para>
		</remarks>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader.Index">
		<summary>
			<para>Gets the location with the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/>
control's <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ColumnHeaderCollection"/>
of this column.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>The zero-based index of the column header within the
   <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ColumnHeaderCollection"/> of the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> control it is contained in.</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>The value of this property does not necessarily correspond to the current
      visual position of the column header within the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/>. This can be due to the user
      reordering the column headers at run time (when the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.AllowColumnReorder"/> property is set to
   <see langword="true"/>). If the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> is not contained within a
   <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> control this property returns a
      value of -1.</para>
		</remarks>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.AllowColumnReorder"/>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader">
		<summary>
			<para> Displays a single column header in a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/>
control.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para> A column header is an item in a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/>
control that contains heading text. <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> objects can be added
to a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> using the
<see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ColumnHeaderCollection.Add"/> method of the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ColumnHeaderCollection"/> class. To add a group of columns to a 
<see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/>, you can use the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ColumnHeaderCollection.AddRange"/> method of 
the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ColumnHeaderCollection"/>
class. You can use the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Index"/> property of the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> class to determine where the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> is located in the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ColumnHeaderCollection"/>
.</para>
			<para><see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> provides the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Text"/>
and <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.TextAlign"/> properties to set the text displayed
in the control and the alignment of the text in the column header. To determine whether
a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> is associated with a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/> control, you can reference the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.ListView"/> property. If you want to
copy a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> for use in another <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/>
control, you can use the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Clone"/> method.</para>
		</remarks>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ColumnHeaderCollection"/>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader.Dispose">
		<nodoc/>
		<summary>
			<para>Disposes of the resources (other than memory) used by
      the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> .</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para>Call <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Dispose"/> when you are finished using
   the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/>. The <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Dispose"/> method
   leaves the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> in an unusable state. After calling
<see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Dispose"/>, you must release all 
   references to the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> so the memory it was occupying can be
   reclaimed by garbage collection. </para>
			<note type="note">
   Always call <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Dispose"/> before you release your last
   reference to the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/>. Otherwise, the resources the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> is using will not be freed until garbage
   collection calls the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> object's destructor.
</note>
		</remarks>
	</doc><doc for="ColumnHeader.Width">
		<summary>
			<para>Gets or sets the width of the column.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>The width of the column, in pixels.</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>This property enables you to set the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Width"/> of the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/>. The <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader"/> can be set to adjust at run time to the 
   column contents or heading. To adjust the width
   of the longest item in the column, set the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Width"/>
   property to -1. To autosize to the width of the column
   heading, set the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.ColumnHeader.Width"/> property to -2.</para>
		</remarks>
	</doc>
</docs>
